  #prepare Data
  load("~/STAT2/2016/proj1/GlioblastomaWide.rda")
  d <- GlioblastomaWide
  rm(GlioblastomaWide)
  d$sampleID <- NULL
  d$Cluster <- NULL
  
  death1y <- d$death1y
  d$death1y <- NULL
  
  test_d = read.csv("~/STAT2/2016/final.csv")
  test_d$Cluster <- NULL
  rowid <- test_d$rowid
  test_d$rowid <- NULL
  
  ncd = ncol(d)
  
  for (i in 1:ncd) {
    if(sum(is.na(d[,ncd+1-i]))>= 10) {
      d[,ncd+1-i] <- NULL
      test_d[,ncd+1-i] <- NULL
    }
  }
  
  for(i in 1:(ncol(d))){
    d[is.na(d[,i]), i] <- mean(d[,i], na.rm = TRUE)
    test_d[is.na(test_d[,i]),i] <- mean(d[,i], na.rm= TRUE)
  }
  
  for(i in 1:(ncol(d))){
    mdi <- mean(d[,i]);
    sdi <- sd(d[,i]);
    d[, i] <- (d[,i] - mdi)/sdi
    test_d[,i] <- (test_d[,i] - mdi)/sdi
  }
  
  X <- as.matrix(d)
  test_d_mat <- as.matrix(test_d)

Model Stacking

model_stacking <- function() {
  train_a_mat <- d_cut[1:62,]
  train_b_mat <- d_cut[63:125,]
  train_a_df <- d_cut_df[1:62,]
  train_b_df <- d_cut_df[63:125,]
  death_a <- death1y[1:62]
  death_b <- death1y[63:125]
  
  glm_a <- cv.glmnet(x = train_a_mat, y=death_a, alpha=0, family="binomial" )
  glm_b <- cv.glmnet(x = train_b_mat, y=death_b, alpha=0, family="binomial" )
  
  glm_a_pred <- predict(glm_b, newx = train_a_mat, s="lambda.min", type="response")
  glm_b_pred <- predict(glm_a, newx = train_b_mat, s="lambda.min", type="response")
  
  glm_f <-rbind(glm_a_pred, glm_b_pred)
  
  svm.model_a <- svm(death1y ~. , data= train_a_df, type="C-classification", probability=TRUE)
  svm.model_b <- svm(death1y ~. , data= train_b_df, type="C-classification", probability=TRUE)
  
  svm_a_pred <- predict(svm.model_b, train_a_df, probability=TRUE)
  svm_b_pred <- predict(svm.model_a, train_b_df, probability=TRUE)
  
  svm_f <- c(attr(svm_a_pred, "probabilities")[,"alive"] , attr(svm_b_pred, "probabilities")[,"alive"])
  
  rf_a <- randomForest(death1y~ . , data=train_a_df)
  rf_b <- randomForest(death1y~ . , data=train_b_df)
  
  pred_rf_a <- predict(rf_b, train_a_df, type="prob")
  pred_rf_b <- predict(rf_a, train_b_df, type="prob")
  
  rf_f <- c(pred_rf_a[,"alive"], pred_rf_b[,"alive"])
  
  #nb_a <-naiveBayes(train_a_mat, train_a_df$death1y) 
  #nb_b <-naiveBayes(train_b_mat, train_b_df$death1y) 
  
  #nb_pred_a <- predict(nb_b, train_a_mat, type="raw")
  #nb_pred_b <- predict(nb_a, train_b_mat, type="raw")
  
  #nb_f <- c(nb_pred_a[,"alive"], nb_pred_b[,"alive"])
  
  new_data <- data.frame(death1y, glm_f, svm_f, rf_f)

  #Compute new features for test data based on predictions for whole training set
  glm_test <- cv.glmnet(x = d_cut, y=death1y, alpha=0, family="binomial" )
  glm_test_f <- predict(glm_test, newx = test_d_cut, s="lambda.min", type="response") 
  
  svm.model_test <- svm(death1y ~. , data= d_cut_df, type="C-classification", probability=TRUE)
  svm_test_pred <- predict(svm.model_test, test_d_cut_df, probability=TRUE)
  svm_test_f <- attr(svm_test_pred, "probabilities")[,"alive"]
  
  rf_test <- randomForest(death1y~ . , data=d_cut_df)
  pred_rf_test <- predict(rf_test, test_d_cut_df, type="prob")
  rf_test_f <- pred_rf_test[,"alive"]
  
  #nb_test <-naiveBayes(d_cut, d_cut_df$death1y) 
  #pred_nb_test <- predict(nb_test, test_d_mat, type="raw")
  #nb_test_f <- pred_nb_test[,"alive"]
  
  new_test <- data.frame(glm_test_f, svm_test_f, rf_test_f)
  colnames(new_test) <- colnames(new_data)[-1]
  
  big_lm <- glm(death1y~. , data=new_data, family="binomial")
  ex_ms <- (predict(big_lm, new_test, type="link") <= 0)
}
